lated star. We discuss the possibility\nthat the companion might be a Wolf-Rayet star that could evolve to become a\nblack hole in 10^4 to 10^5 yr. If so, this would be the first identified\nprogenitor of a neutron star--black hole binary.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Apr 2004 20:42:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Sep 2004 18:48:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
